result.execSummary:
The defendant Roby M Parker was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Sexual Intercourse with Child Age 15 or Older, Actor Under 19, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.093.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant appears in person, in custody from the Waupaca County Jail. Attorney Rose Yanke appears for the state of Wisconsin. Attorney Gavin Grubofski appears in person for defendant.

Court orders time served. DAs office will have until the end of the day to determine when/where defendant will be extradited. If they do not make the determination by the end of today, defendant can be released.

9:39 AM Defendant Roby M Parker appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Gavin Grubofski in court for Roby M Parker.  Prosecuting attorney Rose Marie Yanke in court for the State of Wisconsin. Investigator Scott Goldberg is sworn and questioned by Attorney Yanke. Testifies to employment, education and training.  Testifies to speaking to the alleged victim. Witness identifies the defendant on the video screen. Witness testifies to what the alleged victim told him about her contact with the defendant.  Cross-examination by Attorney Grubofski.  Questions witness regarding the age of the victim and the age of the defendant at the time of the incident.

Attorney Grubofski argues that Count 1 should be amended to a misdemeanor based on the statute.  

Court so amends and proceeds to a plea hearing.
Preliminary hearing and Arraignment on October 17, 2022 at 09:30 am.
Demand for Discovery and Inspection - Defendant
